text: Godman's tree frog (Tlalocohyla godmani) is a frog that lives in Mexico. It lives in highlands in Puebla and Veracruz. This frog has been observed as high as 900 meters above sea level. This frog is in some danger of dying out because human beings change the mesic forest in which it lives and because of pollution from mining. ==References== Category:Frogs of North America
title: Godman's tree frog
